BRONKHORSTSPRUIT - The taxi driver involved in last week's crash near Bronkhorstspruit is being buried in Wolvenkop, Mpumalanga on Saturday.Eighteen school children and two adults died, when a minibus taxi collided with a truck last week Friday.READ: Father shares grief of losing all his children in Verena taxi crashThe minibus, caught fire, trapping its passengers, mainly pupils from two schools.Eyewitnesses suggest the taxi driver turned in front of the oncoming truck.Memorial services will be held at the schools on Wednesday and a public one at the Verena Open Ground the next day.eNCA